Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal, and in particular Article 251 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3817/90 (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3835/92 (2), lays down detailed rules for the application of the supplementary trade mechanism in the eggs and poultrymeat sectors and, in particular, for 1993,  the indicative ceilings for certain products from the said sectors which may be imported into Portugal from the other Member States;
Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 743/93 of 17 March 1993 on the list of products subject to the supplementary trade mechanism and exported to Portugal (3) repeals application of the supplementary trade mechanism in the eggs and poultrymeat sectors  from 1 April 1993; whereas, therefore, the products concerned are not subject to the said mechanism from 1 April 1993;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Eggs and Poultrymeat,
